                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1938: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-07T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 7, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5604. Following telegram has been received from Tehran:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of telegram No. 361, November 6, 5 p.m., from the Minister in
                    Iran, printed on <ref target="#pg_179">page 179</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Please urgently advise Foreign Office that we hope British authorities will
                    proceed with utmost caution and regard for Iranian sensibilities in any action
                    which they may take with respect to alleged conspirators. We consider it
                    especially desirable that no public action of any kind be taken against Iranian
                    nationals until tension caused by wheat and currency problems has relaxed.<note
                        n="60" xml:id="d198fn60">The foregoing paragraph was repeated to the
                        Minister in Iran as Department’s No. 311, November 7, 8 p.m., with the
                        following instruction: “In your discretion you may inform British
                        authorities Tehran that above represents Department’s attitude.”
                        (891.00/1937)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
